1. Definitions

   1.1 "Software" means the Prompt Universe repository and all of its contents,
       including source code, Lisp definitions, documentation, configuration
       files, seed prompts, expansion plans, example outputs, scripts, published
       variant batches, and accompanying materials, whether in source or
       compiled form.

   1.2 "Generated Output" means prompt text, markdown files, variant batches,
       reports, logs, images, and other materials You create by running or
       extending the Software. Generated Output is separate from the Software
       itself.

   1.3 "You" means an individual exercising permissions granted by this License,
       or a legal entity on behalf of which an individual is exercising those
       permissions.

   1.4 "Fan Use" means personal, hobby, or creative use by fans and individual
       users, including making images for Yourself, experimenting with prompts,
       learning the toolchain, and sharing Generated Output non-commercially.

   1.5 "Personal Use" means use by You for Yourself where the primary purpose
       is not revenue generation or commercial advantage, including private
       study, personal creative projects, hobby work, and non-profit education.

   1.6 "Non-Commercial Use" means Fan Use, Personal Use, or any other use that
       is not Commercial Use.

   1.7 "Commercial Use" means any use, reproduction, distribution,
       sublicensing, sale, rental, lease, hosting for pay, or other exploitation
       primarily intended to obtain monetary compensation or commercial
       advantage, whether direct or indirect, including but not limited to:

       (a) selling or licensing the Software, any Modified Version, or access to
           them;
       (b) selling or licensing prompt packs, prompt libraries, template packs,
           courses, workshops, subscriptions, or consulting derived from or
           substantially based on the Software, its seeds, plans, or published
           batches;
       (c) operating a paid service, SaaS, API, app, marketplace listing, or
           membership offering powered by the Software or its outputs;
       (d) using the Software in client work, commissioned work, or production
           workflows billed to a third party;
       (e) using the Software in the ordinary revenue-generating business of a
           for-profit organization;
       (f) fundraising or crowdfunding where the Software or its outputs are a
           primary deliverable or selling point;
       (g) any use that would require a commercial license if the Licensor
           offered one.

   1.8 "Licensor" means Licca Bobo, the copyright holder of the Software.

   1.9 "Modified Version" means any work based on or incorporating the
       Software, including translations, adaptations, derivative repositories,
